1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 25:742, relative to historic preservation districts; to provide
3 relative to historic district commission powers; to provide relative to bid
4 requirements; to provide relative to a certificate of appropriateness from the historic
5 preservation district commission; to provide relative to a historic preservation
6 commission authorization to institute civil proceedings in certain circumstances; and
7 to provide for related matters.
8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
9 Section 1. R.S. 25:742 is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
10 §742. Applicability of historic district commission powers
11 A. It is the intent and purpose of this Chapter that the regulatory powers
12 conferred by it on an historic preservation district commission, created under its
13 authority, shall apply to all private property, in the area controlled by it, including
14 all buildings, structures, areas, sites, and their adjuncts and appurtenances, insofar
15 as they constitute part of the entirety or tout ensemble of the historic section. Any
16 governmental agency of the state or local government, other than the governing
17 body, having a responsibility for any building, structure, area, site, public way and
18 their adjuncts and appurtenances within the historic preservation site shall seek the
19 advice of the historic district commission prior to the initiation of any substantive
20 change, modification, renovation, restoration or construction a new construction
21 project in the locally designated historic district.
22 B. Except for state infrastructure projects, a state or local governmental
23 agency shall not commence a new construction project within a locally
24 designated historic district or at a locally designated landmark unless a
25 certificate of appropriateness has been issued by the historic preservation
26 district commission with jurisdiction over the locally designated historic district
27 or locally designated landmark, unless the commission waives this requirement.
